Marcellum: M. Claudius Marcellus, consul in 51 B.C.‚ was a strong partisan of the senate in their breach with Caesar. In Lucan (i 313) he is called by Caesar loquax, ‘the man of words' ; and he certainly took little part in the war. After Pharsalia he retired to Mytilene and devoted himself to study ;· when allowed by Caesar to return to Italy, he was murdered in Athens on his way home (46 B.C.).
